173
00:13:09.875 --> 00:13:11.529
- [laughs]
- [laughs] What?


174
00:13:12.399 --> 00:13:13.357
That's not true.

175
00:13:14.488 --> 00:13:15.925
It took months
for you to talk to me.


176
00:13:17.013 --> 00:13:18.666
He would just follow me

177
00:13:18.710 --> 00:13:20.320
and then run away whenever
I looked at him. [chuckles]


178
00:13:22.757 --> 00:13:23.802
[Raymond]
Let me ask you a question.


179
00:13:26.413 --> 00:13:28.328
What do you intend
to do about this?


180
00:13:31.679 --> 00:13:35.335
When the baby comes, and judging from
your size, that will be relatively soon,


181
00:13:35.379 --> 00:13:38.208
when the baby comes, there will
be no hospitals or doctors.


182
00:13:38.251 --> 00:13:39.426
So, how do you intend
to have it?


183
00:13:41.037 --> 00:13:43.300
And once it's born,
how do you intend to raise it


184
00:13:43.343 --> 00:13:46.651
in a world where only the
strong survive, the weak perish?


185
00:13:47.260 --> 00:13:50.220
Have either of you thought
for one minute...


186
00:13:51.786 --> 00:13:54.180
about the repercussions of
your irresponsible behavior?


187
00:13:54.224 --> 00:13:56.008
[Ray laughs]

188
00:13:57.140 --> 00:13:57.792
[clears throat]

189
00:13:59.707 --> 00:14:00.839
It's really good to be home.

190
00:14:13.895 --> 00:14:15.114
[music stops]

191
00:14:20.380 --> 00:14:21.729
[beeping]

192
00:14:31.565 --> 00:14:32.871
When are they coming
for us, Fred?


193
00:14:45.449 --> 00:14:49.105
I'm gonna prove to you
that I can take care of you.


194
00:14:53.239 --> 00:14:54.023
I love you.

195
00:15:09.299 --> 00:15:10.256
[beeps]

196
