[knocking]

199
00:16:30.858 --> 00:16:32.295
Awake? Hmm.

200
00:16:40.216 --> 00:16:41.130
Up and at 'em, okay?

201
00:16:41.826 --> 00:16:42.827
Breakfast.

202
00:16:47.614 --> 00:16:48.876
We're gonna be okay.

203
00:16:56.319 --> 00:16:57.494
Your hair looks pretty.

204
00:16:58.669 --> 00:16:59.713
Okay.

205
00:17:02.760 --> 00:17:03.848
Is it gonna start
getting cold?


206
00:17:05.023 --> 00:17:05.980
We have plenty of heat.

207
00:17:06.851 --> 00:17:07.808
We have plenty of warmth.

208
00:17:09.114 --> 00:17:09.897
Okay?

209
00:17:12.509 --> 00:17:13.988
[muffled crying]

210
00:17:30.918 --> 00:17:31.789
I'm sorry.

211
00:17:34.444 --> 00:17:35.227
Breakfast is ready.

212
00:17:44.715 --> 00:17:45.846
[shaky breathing]

213
00:17:47.326 --> 00:17:48.327
Thank you.

214
00:17:51.287 --> 00:17:52.462
Is he going to stay up there
all day again?


215
00:17:55.247 --> 00:17:56.814
I'll go check on him.Ah.

216
00:17:56.857 --> 00:17:57.902
How good of you to join us.

217
00:18:05.518 --> 00:18:06.867
What? You guys don't
know what today is?


218
00:18:07.868 --> 00:18:09.435
What day is it?

219
00:18:09.479 --> 00:18:12.221
Well, my dear sister, today
is the first day of spring.


220
00:18:14.179 --> 00:18:15.659
The flowers have bloomed,
the birds are singing,


221
00:18:15.702 --> 00:18:16.486
and the sun is shining.

222
00:18:16.529 --> 00:18:17.878
[dog barking]

223
00:18:18.705 --> 00:18:19.489
He's barking again.

224
00:18:20.664 --> 00:18:21.708
Maybe he needs help.

225
00:18:23.710 --> 00:18:24.842
You've gotta eat something.

226
00:18:25.886 --> 00:18:27.018
You're gonna hurt
the baby if you don't.


227
00:18:29.934 --> 00:18:31.501
Darling, please eat something.

228
00:18:31.936 --> 00:18:34.112
Fred, I found that old axe
in the basement.


229
00:18:34.155 --> 00:18:37.376
Maybe you and I could go and
chop some wood after breakfast.


230
00:18:37.420 --> 00:18:39.552
Yeah, that's fine--I'm sorry,
I can't do this anymore.


231
00:18:40.379 --> 00:18:41.946
When are they coming for us?

232
00:18:44.949 --> 00:18:46.124
Please, for God's sake!

233
00:18:47.647 --> 00:18:49.170
Dad, I'm sorry--No, no. Fred, it's okay.
It's all right.


234
00:18:49.475 --> 00:18:51.216
She's just worried
about her survival.


235
00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:53.566
To be honest, I'd be
concerned if she weren't.


236
00:18:55.699 --> 00:18:57.091
Do you pray at night, Margot?

237
00:18:59.442 --> 00:19:01.182
I've never been
a man of faith myself.


238
00:19:01.922 --> 00:19:03.272
I'm a practical man.

239
00:19:05.186 --> 00:19:07.624
I think life is simple. If you live a
life of integrity and responsibility,


240
00:19:07.667 --> 00:19:08.451
then you're rewarded.

241
00:19:09.016 --> 00:19:10.540
My conscious is clear.

242
00:19:11.584 --> 00:19:12.933
You can't do this anymore?

243
00:19:14.587 --> 00:19:15.893
Well, there's the door.

244
00:19:17.590 --> 00:19:18.461
And nobody's going to stop you
and I'm sure God will go with you.


245
00:19:19.723 --> 00:19:21.942
They'll come for us
when they come for us,


246
00:19:21.986 --> 00:19:25.032
and my family will wait
as long as we have to.


247
00:19:28.166 --> 00:19:29.994
You're lying. Margot, please...

248
00:19:30.299 --> 00:19:31.691
Who do you think you are?

249
00:19:33.432 --> 00:19:35.042
- Just because you found your
golden ticket, -What are you--


250
00:19:35.086 --> 00:19:37.044
you think you can come into
my house and call me a liar?


251
00:19:38.002 --> 00:19:40.918
You sit here,
eat my food in my house.


252
00:19:40.961 --> 00:19:41.962
Who do you think you are?

253
00:19:45.618 --> 00:19:46.793
[dog barking in the distance]

254
00:19:52.495 --> 00:19:53.974
Clara, for God's sake, stop
fidgeting!


255
00:20:03.941 --> 00:20:04.985
Gina.

256
00:20:12.515 --> 00:20:13.167
[whistles]

257
00:20:19.522 --> 00:20:20.784
Too freakin' sunny in here.

258
00:20:24.657 --> 00:20:26.137
[Margot] I can't be
here one more second.


259
00:20:27.094 --> 00:20:28.139
We're safe here.

260
00:20:29.532 --> 00:20:30.707
It's freezing outside--

261
00:20:30.750 --> 00:20:32.056
I want to go home!

262
00:20:32.099 --> 00:20:33.927
I want to call my family!

263
00:20:34.406 --> 00:20:36.365
I want to use the house phone!

264
00:20:36.843 --> 00:20:38.497
We're waiting for someone
to come get us. When?


265
00:20:39.455 --> 00:20:41.805
You promised me we'd be safe.

266
00:20:41.848 --> 00:20:43.894
There's just other people
they have to pick up first.


267
00:20:43.937 --> 00:20:45.112
We have to wait.

268
00:20:46.244 --> 00:20:47.767
We are just waiting for death.

269
00:20:53.991 --> 00:20:55.035
Hey.

270
00:20:56.689 --> 00:20:58.430
Hey, we are not
just waiting for death, okay?


271
00:21:00.301 --> 00:21:01.302
We're waiting for her.

272
00:21:03.957 --> 00:21:06.133
When she comes,
everything will be better.


273
00:21:14.098 --> 00:21:15.142
She's safe.

274
00:21:20.887 --> 00:21:22.149
[dog barking in the distance]

275
00:21:29.287 --> 00:21:30.462
[wood splitting]

276
00:21:55.966 --> 00:21:56.532
There!

277
00:21:57.184 --> 00:21:58.534
Okay. [grunts]

278
00:21:59.230 --> 00:22:00.144
Let's see. Go look.

279
00:22:04.670 --> 00:22:06.280
[chuckles]

280
00:22:07.543 --> 00:22:09.370
You know, you're pretty
good at this.


281
00:22:10.720 --> 00:22:11.590
Abbey used to do it to me.

282
00:22:12.548 --> 00:22:13.723
She wore it all the time.

283
00:22:14.811 --> 00:22:16.421
I think that's why boys
liked her so much.


284
00:22:16.813 --> 00:22:17.553
Who's Abbey?

285
00:22:18.031 --> 00:22:19.076
You can't go in there.

286
00:22:20.120 --> 00:22:20.904
Why not?

287
00:22:22.340 --> 00:22:23.820
[piano music playing]

288
00:22:23.863 --> 00:22:24.647
We're not supposed to.

289
00:22:27.780 --> 00:22:29.390
I'll be right in.Okay.

290
00:22:29.956 --> 00:22:32.045
[tools clatter]

291
00:22:34.047 --> 00:22:35.832
[muffled piano playing]

292
00:22:51.500 --> 00:22:53.502
[engine turns over]

293
00:23:24.707 --> 00:23:26.317
[music stops]

294
00:23:27.057 --> 00:23:28.101
Clara did it.

295
00:23:29.015 --> 00:23:29.799
Isn't it nice?

296
00:23:36.327 --> 00:23:38.329
[music resumes]

297
00:23:44.465 --> 00:23:45.379
Fred. Hmm?

298
00:23:47.599 --> 00:23:48.382
Who's Abbey?

299
00:23:52.778 --> 00:23:53.562
She was my sister.

300
00:23:55.128 --> 00:23:56.347
She died five years ago.

301
00:23:57.783 --> 00:23:58.654
I'm so sorry.

302
00:23:59.132 --> 00:24:00.438
Why didn't you tell me?

303
00:24:01.004 --> 00:24:02.353
Let's not talk about this, okay?

304
00:24:10.753 --> 00:24:13.233
Can we spend all day
together tomorrow?


305
00:24:14.104 --> 00:24:15.061
What's tomorrow?

306
00:24:18.412 --> 00:24:19.196
Mom.

307
00:24:20.414 --> 00:24:21.198
Hey, Mom.

308
00:24:22.678 --> 00:24:23.592
Yes?

309
00:24:23.983 --> 00:24:25.594
Can I dress up
for my birthday?


310
00:24:26.246 --> 00:24:27.073
Yes.

311
00:24:33.645 --> 00:24:34.864
[engine turn off]

312
00:24:34.907 --> 00:24:36.256
[upbeat piano music playing]

313
00:24:57.451 --> 00:24:59.236
How are you? I'm fine.

314
00:25:00.193 --> 00:25:01.020
Darling.

315
00:25:01.064 --> 00:25:01.891
[both chuckle]

316
00:25:14.643 --> 00:25:16.645
I know we don't really
get to talk about Abbey.


317
00:25:20.387 --> 00:25:22.607
I'm sorry I couldn't be here.

318
00:25:25.349 --> 00:25:26.872
That was a really horrible day.

319
00:25:29.701 --> 00:25:30.484
Please. I'm fine.

320
00:25:33.270 --> 00:25:34.880
You've got to stop saying
that you're fine.


321
00:25:35.402 --> 00:25:36.969
Not when it sounds
like you're not.


322
00:25:37.013 --> 00:25:38.144
I don't want to talk about it.

323
00:25:39.450 --> 00:25:40.581
It's okay to talk about it.

324
00:25:40.625 --> 00:25:41.844
No, it's not okay
to talk about it.


325
00:25:41.887 --> 00:25:43.584
Yes, it is.
It's okay to talk about it.


326
00:25:43.628 --> 00:25:45.674
Haven't we all
been through enough?


327
00:25:45.717 --> 00:25:47.632
Why do you insist
on talking about it?


328
00:25:48.024 --> 00:25:50.156
- Clara! Get off of that piano!
- [piano playing stops]


329
00:25:51.201 --> 00:25:52.637
Why? Because I said so!

330
00:25:58.948 --> 00:25:59.905
[sighs]

331
00:26:00.471 --> 00:26:01.515
I'm fine.

332
00:26:02.255 --> 00:26:03.300
I'm fine.

333
00:26:19.055 --> 00:26:20.404
[laughter echoing]

334
00:26:35.854 --> 00:26:36.899
Mom?

335
00:26:38.988 --> 00:26:40.076
Are you mad at me?

336
00:26:44.080 --> 00:26:45.124
No.

337
00:26:48.432 --> 00:26:50.390
How could I be mad
at my little baby?


338
00:26:52.001 --> 00:26:53.393
Oh.

339
00:26:53.437 --> 00:26:54.655
My darling little bunny.

340
00:26:56.266 --> 00:26:57.876
Oh, I've missed you.

341
00:27:03.316 --> 00:27:04.578
You mustn't go running off now.

342
00:27:05.492 --> 00:27:06.493
Mommy gets worried.

343
00:27:09.366 --> 00:27:11.281
Oh, you grew up so fast.

344
00:27:13.892 --> 00:27:14.719
Mom?

345
00:27:15.633 --> 00:27:16.503
You're hurting me.

346
00:27:30.430 --> 00:27:31.388
I'm tired.

347
00:27:33.607 --> 00:27:34.391
It's time for bed.

348
00:27:38.047 --> 00:27:39.091
Let me rest, Clara.

349
00:27:49.319 --> 00:27:51.712
[Raymond] Look, I don't know
what the hold-up is here, but...


350
00:27:53.323 --> 00:27:56.761
I am running pretty low on patience so
if you could just give me a time frame.


351
00:27:57.893 --> 00:27:59.546
I've got a house
full of people here and...


352
00:28:00.634 --> 00:28:01.592
and...

353
00:28:03.333 --> 00:28:05.074
I practically got you your fucking
nomination, you son of a bitch!


354
00:28:05.117 --> 00:28:06.205
You owe me, Bill.

355
00:28:06.249 --> 00:28:07.032
You promised me!

356
00:28:10.470 --> 00:28:11.297
Bill, I'm sorry.

357
00:28:13.299 --> 00:28:14.387
I'm sorry, um...

358
00:28:15.606 --> 00:28:16.476
Just--

359
00:28:16.520 --> 00:28:17.608
Just give me a call, okay?

360
00:28:17.651 --> 00:28:21.264
Or just answer your phone.

361
00:28:22.395 --> 00:28:23.614
Will you do that, old friend?

362
00:28:24.789 --> 00:28:25.572
Okay?

363
00:28:27.618 --> 00:28:28.662
Okay.

364
00:28:29.750 --> 00:28:30.447
[beeps]

365
00:28:32.275 --> 00:28:33.580
[sighs]

366
00:28:39.021 --> 00:28:39.630
[knocking on door]

367
00:28:40.196 --> 00:28:41.414
[door opens]

368
00:28:44.113 --> 00:28:44.896
Hey.

369
00:28:47.725 --> 00:28:48.900
Is it time?

370
00:28:48.944 --> 00:28:51.120
No, no, no. It's tomorrow.

371
00:28:55.385 --> 00:28:56.168
Happy birthday.

372
00:29:03.480 --> 00:29:04.829
[both chuckle]

373
00:29:08.702 --> 00:29:09.486
Good job.[giggles]

374
00:29:15.666 --> 00:29:16.754
You want to go see
something cool?


375
00:29:19.365 --> 00:29:21.063
Hmm? Hmm?

376
00:29:22.281 --> 00:29:23.282
Come on, let's go.

377
00:29:25.415 --> 00:29:26.720
[steam hissing]

378
00:29:26.764 --> 00:29:27.504
[Clara] We're gonna
get in trouble.


379
00:29:29.549 --> 00:29:31.247
Dad doesn't like
when we go outside at nighttime.


380
00:29:32.248 --> 00:29:33.249
[Ray] It's always nighttime.

381
00:29:39.559 --> 00:29:40.604
What is it?

382
00:29:40.996 --> 00:29:41.779
I don't know.

383
00:29:45.696 --> 00:29:47.089
This is cool.Yeah.

384
00:29:48.481 --> 00:29:49.308
Happy birthday, Clara.

385
00:29:52.398 --> 00:29:53.443
Ray.

386
00:29:54.705 --> 00:29:55.880
Promise you won't leave.

387
00:29:55.924 --> 00:29:57.447
[steam hissing]

388
00:29:57.490 --> 00:29:58.752
[sighs] Clara... Just...

389
00:30:00.015 --> 00:30:00.841
Promise?

390
00:30:01.407 --> 00:30:03.409
[steam hissing]

391
00:30:03.453 --> 00:30:04.628
I promise.

392
00:30:07.152 --> 00:30:08.197
Come on.

393
00:30:09.372 --> 00:30:10.721
[steam hissing]

394
00:30:22.124 --> 00:30:23.168
[dog barking]

395
00:30:30.610 --> 00:30:31.655
Perfect.

396
00:30:32.438 --> 00:30:33.483
What do you think?

397
00:30:34.397 --> 00:30:35.920
Best cake ever.

398
00:30:38.575 --> 00:30:39.968
- Mom.
- What?


399
00:30:40.838 --> 00:30:42.448
You're not too old
for that, are you?


400
00:30:42.883 --> 00:30:43.536
Never too old for that.Yep.

401
00:30:44.233 --> 00:30:45.712
[laughs]

402
00:30:49.107 --> 00:30:50.152
Good.

403
00:30:50.195 --> 00:30:51.240
I can't do it.

404
00:30:52.763 --> 00:30:54.895
There should be some candles
in the drawers over there.


405
00:30:59.857 --> 00:31:01.337
Mom? Hmm? Yeah.

406
00:31:04.296 --> 00:31:05.210
You should go get dressed.

407
00:31:14.306 --> 00:31:15.916
[dog barking in the distance]

408
00:31:19.703 --> 00:31:21.096
[classical piano music playing]

409
00:31:22.358 --> 00:31:23.315
[Raymond]
Where's the birthday girl?


410
00:31:24.360 --> 00:31:25.535
Clara, we're waiting!

411
00:31:26.797 --> 00:31:28.451
[Raymond sighs] Oh, that dog.

412
00:31:32.150 --> 00:31:32.977
Clara?

413
00:31:41.246 --> 00:31:42.117
You think this is funny?

414
00:31:45.076 --> 00:31:46.817
Mom said that I could dress up.

415
00:31:49.472 --> 00:31:50.255
What is it with you?

416
00:31:55.304 --> 00:31:56.783
I'm sorry-
-Off. Now.

417
00:32:11.320 --> 00:32:12.712
[barking]

418
00:32:32.297 --> 00:32:34.082
[crickets chirping]

419
00:33:06.592 --> 00:33:09.247
[Raymond panting]

420
00:33:30.442 --> 00:33:31.139
[lock clicks]

421
00:33:43.629 --> 00:33:44.761
It still looks good.

422
00:33:46.154 --> 00:33:47.242
Thanks.[Raymond]
It's time to cut the cake.


423
00:33:50.723 --> 00:33:51.768
Is he dead?

424
00:33:53.639 --> 00:33:54.988
- What?
- The dog.


425
00:33:56.033 --> 00:33:57.165
You didn't kill him, did you?

426
00:33:58.905 --> 00:33:59.950
No, no, no.

427
00:34:00.733 --> 00:34:01.778
Where's that cake?

428
00:34:04.650 --> 00:34:05.912
My little girl's birthday.

429
00:34:07.262 --> 00:34:08.088
We can't yet.

430
00:34:08.959 --> 00:34:10.134
We're waiting for Ray.

431
00:34:10.178 --> 00:34:11.179
Oh, never mind him.

432
00:34:13.050 --> 00:34:14.573
Do you want to tell me what you
two were doing outside last night?


433
00:34:14.617 --> 00:34:15.574
[scratching under table]

434
00:34:18.708 --> 00:34:19.274
Don't fidget.

435
00:34:20.666 --> 00:34:21.928
Don't bother lying to me.

436
00:34:23.321 --> 00:34:24.366
Why were you outside?

437
00:34:30.023 --> 00:34:32.504
Clara, I thought I made
myself perfectly clear.


438
00:34:32.548 --> 00:34:34.289
I don't want you going
outside at nighttime.


439
00:34:36.726 --> 00:34:39.207
- It's always nighttime. -I don't
want you going outside, period.


440
00:34:39.555 --> 00:34:42.210
Not at night, not during
the day, not any time.


441
00:34:42.253 --> 00:34:43.907
Do you understand
why I'm telling you this?


442
00:34:47.650 --> 00:34:48.694
Do you really?

443
00:34:53.221 --> 00:34:56.224
Because here we have warmth.

444
00:34:56.659 --> 00:34:57.442
We have food.

445
00:34:57.877 --> 00:34:58.791
We're safe.

446
00:34:59.139 --> 00:35:01.011
I am trying to take care of you.

447
00:35:02.447 --> 00:35:04.884
All of you! Why do you make it
so goddamn hard?


448
00:35:06.843 --> 00:35:07.887
Don't cry.

449
00:35:08.323 --> 00:35:09.498
Look at me, Clara.

450
00:35:09.541 --> 00:35:10.890
Look at me. Don't cry.

451
00:35:11.630 --> 00:35:12.588
Do not cry.

452
00:35:13.850 --> 00:35:14.894
Do you understand?

453
00:35:17.332 --> 00:35:19.899
You understand why it's not safe
to go outside?


454
00:35:23.990 --> 00:35:26.515
♪ Happy birthday to you

455
00:35:27.646 --> 00:35:30.606
[all] ♪ Happy birthday to you

456
00:35:31.520 --> 00:35:35.045
♪ Happy birthday, dear Clara

457
00:35:35.785 --> 00:35:38.875
♪ Happy birthday to you

458
00:35:40.268 --> 00:35:40.920
Make a wish, Clara.

459
00:36:09.645 --> 00:36:11.864
[opera music plays]

460
00:36:32.581 --> 00:36:33.886
[snickers]

461
00:36:38.326 --> 00:36:40.153
[Margot laughs]

462
00:36:55.908 --> 00:36:57.345
[all laughing]

463
00:37:07.746 --> 00:37:10.096
- [music grows louder]
- [laughing continues]


464
00:37:42.259 --> 00:37:44.043
[muffled laughing]

465
00:37:48.787 --> 00:37:50.572
[chuckles]

466
00:38:00.799 --> 00:38:02.540
[wind howls]

467
00:38:08.024 --> 00:38:09.199
[sighs]

468
00:38:10.156 --> 00:38:11.114
I'm sorry.

469
00:38:12.550 --> 00:38:13.986
Sorry I haven't
been there for you.


470
00:38:16.989 --> 00:38:18.121
You're going to be a dad.

471
00:38:20.732 --> 00:38:22.168
You have a girl that loves you.

472
00:38:25.215 --> 00:38:26.216
And you're happy.

473
00:38:26.738 --> 00:38:27.783
Aren't you?

474
00:38:33.832 --> 00:38:35.225
You know, I keep having
this dream,


475
00:38:36.444 --> 00:38:37.836
over and over again,
the same one.


476
00:38:40.317 --> 00:38:42.667
I'm holding her in my arms.
Claudine.


477
00:38:42.711 --> 00:38:43.755
Hmm.

478
00:38:45.017 --> 00:38:47.193
She's the size
of a bread crumb.[chuckles]


479
00:38:48.804 --> 00:38:49.587
So small.

480
00:38:52.024 --> 00:38:54.157
And I'm just so scared
I'm going to drop her.


481
00:38:55.767 --> 00:38:56.812
And I do.

482
00:38:57.552 --> 00:38:58.378
I drop her.

483
00:39:02.034 --> 00:39:03.166
It's only a dream, Fred.

484
00:39:07.823 --> 00:39:08.911
We shouldn't be outside.

485
00:39:29.366 --> 00:39:30.585
[shivering]

486
00:39:36.286 --> 00:39:38.244
Sorry. I didn't
mean to scare you.


487
00:39:38.288 --> 00:39:39.419
Uh, you didn't. It's just...

488
00:39:40.072 --> 00:39:41.639
It's usually just me
up at this time.


489
00:39:43.119 --> 00:39:44.337
I couldn't sleep.

490
00:39:44.381 --> 00:39:45.425
I'm sorry.

491
00:39:45.687 --> 00:39:46.514
No, no, no. It's fine.

492
00:39:48.124 --> 00:39:49.168
What are you reading?

493
00:39:50.866 --> 00:39:51.910
[sighs]

494
00:39:56.436 --> 00:39:57.350
[scoffs]

495
00:39:58.917 --> 00:39:59.701
I thought...

496
00:40:01.659 --> 00:40:03.705
just in case
I never get to meet her,


497
00:40:06.142 --> 00:40:08.187
at least I would know
what it would be like...


498
00:40:09.798 --> 00:40:10.581
to have her.

499
00:40:13.802 --> 00:40:14.716
It's silly.

500
00:40:19.024 --> 00:40:20.069
Why did you leave?

501
00:40:23.246 --> 00:40:25.378
I just couldn't deal anymore, you know?
I couldn't...


502
00:40:28.947 --> 00:40:30.079
With everything that happened.

503
00:40:31.559 --> 00:40:32.821
I heard about your sister.

504
00:40:35.824 --> 00:40:36.607
I'm sorry.

505
00:40:39.871 --> 00:40:41.438
[clears throat] Yeah, well,
that was a long time ago.


506
00:40:43.614 --> 00:40:44.963
Yeah. It's late.
I'm gonna actually...


507
00:40:46.182 --> 00:40:47.400
try and get some sleep.

508
00:40:49.707 --> 00:40:50.752
What happened to her?

509
00:40:56.105 --> 00:40:57.367
Our father killed her.

510
00:41:05.462 --> 00:41:06.942
[clears throat][beeps]

511
00:41:13.949 --> 00:41:14.863
[sighs]

512
00:41:24.960 --> 00:41:26.004
I love you, too.

513
00:41:28.528 --> 00:41:29.617
I miss you so much.

514
00:41:31.096 --> 00:41:32.707
Every night I go outside

515
00:41:32.750 --> 00:41:35.361
and I look up at the stars
like we used to.


516
00:41:38.147 --> 00:41:39.496
I don't know if I can do this.

517
00:41:42.978 --> 00:41:46.242
It's... This is way
worse than I remember.


518
00:41:51.029 --> 00:41:52.030
I can't.

519
00:41:52.640 --> 00:41:53.423
No, I can't.

520
00:41:56.034 --> 00:41:57.514
They're still my family.

521
00:41:57.775 --> 00:41:59.385
I need to be here for Clara.
She needs me.


522
00:42:00.735 --> 00:42:01.736
I can't leave her again.

523
00:42:04.434 --> 00:42:05.435
[beeps]

524
00:42:05.478 --> 00:42:07.785
This is not to be used...
by anyone.


525
00:42:09.004 --> 00:42:10.048
Understood?

526
00:42:13.443 --> 00:42:15.358
At least you had the good sense
not to bring her here with you.


527
00:42:15.924 --> 00:42:18.317
Well, nobody deserves
to spend their last days here.


528
00:42:52.525 --> 00:42:54.440
[Raymond] You, my dear,
are nothing!


529
00:42:54.876 --> 00:42:55.964
You're nothing!

530
00:42:56.007 --> 00:42:57.226
You do not exist!

531
00:42:57.269 --> 00:42:59.707
Do you understand me?
You don't exist!


532
00:43:33.088 --> 00:43:34.132
She's here.

533
00:43:40.748 --> 00:43:41.487
Come on now, Gina.

534
00:43:42.662 --> 00:43:43.794
You better get
a start on dinner.


535
00:43:45.448 --> 00:43:46.623
She's always been here.

536
00:43:47.015 --> 00:43:48.581
No. She hasn't.

537
00:43:49.800 --> 00:43:51.062
Abbey is dead. 
You know that.

538
00:43:51.410 --> 00:43:52.455
No.

539
00:43:53.848 --> 00:43:54.892
No.

540
00:43:57.939 --> 00:43:59.288
Don't fall apart on me now.

541
00:44:01.377 --> 00:44:02.421
We're almost there.

542
00:44:05.250 --> 00:44:06.556
Why didn't we help her?

543
00:44:09.167 --> 00:44:11.779
Why didn't we understand?
She was just a child.


544
00:44:22.050 --> 00:44:22.833
You don't even care.

545
00:44:24.400 --> 00:44:25.923
You think I don't miss her?

546
00:44:25.967 --> 00:44:27.882
You think I don't think
about her every single day?


547
00:44:27.925 --> 00:44:29.971
Then why didn't you
let me go after her?


548
00:44:30.014 --> 00:44:31.233
Why did you stop me?

549
00:44:35.585 --> 00:44:36.629
Take your medicine. 
I don't want it.

550
00:44:36.673 --> 00:44:38.675
- Take your medicine!
- No! No!


551
00:44:38.718 --> 00:44:39.807
Gina, take your medicine!

552
00:44:39.850 --> 00:44:40.808
It's all your fault!

553
00:44:41.025 --> 00:44:42.592
[gasps] It's all your fault!

554
00:44:43.245 --> 00:44:44.768
No, it's your fault!

555
00:44:44.812 --> 00:44:45.856
It's your fault!

556
00:44:45.900 --> 00:44:47.162
You couldn't take care of her.

557
00:44:47.205 --> 00:44:48.424
Look at you!

558
00:44:49.904 --> 00:44:51.340
Look at you now. You can't
even take care of yourself.


559
00:44:52.210 --> 00:44:53.168
[whimpers]

560
00:44:59.174 --> 00:45:01.306
I can't take care
of our family without you.


561
00:45:02.351 --> 00:45:04.179
I cannot lose you again.

562
00:45:09.706 --> 00:45:10.489
This is the only way.

563
00:45:11.751 --> 00:45:12.535
You need them.

564
00:45:31.859 --> 00:45:32.685
[sighs]

565
00:45:37.429 --> 00:45:38.474
Rest.

566
00:45:38.996 --> 00:45:40.476
Things will be better
in the morning.


567
00:45:42.391 --> 00:45:43.435
You'll see.

568
00:45:46.438 --> 00:45:47.526
I'll make dinner tonight.

569
00:45:50.965 --> 00:45:52.967
I'm thinking risotto.

570
00:45:56.057 --> 00:45:57.275
[door closes]

571
00:45:57.319 --> 00:45:59.495
[squeaking]

572
00:46:32.136 --> 00:46:33.529
[air hissing]

573
00:46:38.012 --> 00:46:38.795
Ah.

574
00:46:41.015 --> 00:46:41.798
See?

575
00:46:44.148 --> 00:46:44.932
Who is that?

576
00:46:46.237 --> 00:46:47.238
That's my sister.

577
00:46:48.196 --> 00:46:49.240
Sophie.

578
00:46:51.373 --> 00:46:52.417
She looks like you.

579
00:46:53.679 --> 00:46:54.942
You must miss your sister a lot.

580
00:46:56.073 --> 00:46:57.074
What happened to Abbey?

581
00:46:59.076 --> 00:47:01.209
I don't remember
Abbey that much.


582
00:47:02.036 --> 00:47:02.732
Is that bad?

583
00:47:03.646 --> 00:47:04.690
[Margot] Of course not.

584
00:47:06.040 --> 00:47:07.563
[Clara] She used to get
in trouble all the time.


585
00:47:10.218 --> 00:47:12.568
Dad would always yell at her and
then everything would be fine.


586
00:47:14.918 --> 00:47:15.701
Not that day.

587
00:47:17.834 --> 00:47:18.966
What happened that day?

588
00:47:21.055 --> 00:47:21.881
That day...

589
00:47:22.970 --> 00:47:24.232
Mom found something of Abbey's.

590
00:47:25.102 --> 00:47:25.973
Something really bad.

591
00:47:28.671 --> 00:47:29.715
She ran away.

592
00:47:32.805 --> 00:47:34.329
They found her body
by the shore.


593
00:47:36.287 --> 00:47:37.680
She ate a bunch
of the bad berries.


594
00:47:39.638 --> 00:47:41.466
We've always known
about the bad berries.


595
00:47:41.510 --> 00:47:42.990
Dad made sure we knew.

596
00:47:44.556 --> 00:47:45.731
What are the bad berries?

597
00:47:47.255 --> 00:47:48.125
They grow all around.

598
00:47:49.213 --> 00:47:50.910
A single one could kill you.

599
00:47:51.476 --> 00:47:52.477
Dad would always tell us.

600
00:47:54.610 --> 00:47:56.090
Dad said it was an accident.

601
00:47:58.135 --> 00:48:00.572
Ray said that
she killed herself.


602
00:48:02.792 --> 00:48:04.446
Ray always told me the truth.

603
00:48:15.413 --> 00:48:16.762
[heavy breathing]

604
00:48:27.556 --> 00:48:28.731
[sobs softly]

605
00:49:18.128 --> 00:49:19.999
[classical music playing]

606
00:49:36.842 --> 00:49:38.540
[scraping]

607
00:49:44.459 --> 00:49:45.590
[muffled laughter]

608
00:49:59.517 --> 00:50:00.866
[laughter continues]

609
00:50:10.702 --> 00:50:12.226
[laughter continues]

610
00:50:19.494 --> 00:50:20.277
Abbey!

611
00:50:21.278 --> 00:50:23.498
Abbey, you sweet girl!

612
00:50:24.847 --> 00:50:27.023
Oh, I'm so sorry! Mom!

613
00:50:27.066 --> 00:50:29.417
- Mrs. Beaty--
- I'm so sorry-- No!


614
00:50:29.460 --> 00:50:30.287
I'm so sorry. [sobbing]

615
00:50:30.331 --> 00:50:31.375
Fred!

616
00:50:33.508 --> 00:50:34.552
Fred!

617
00:50:37.599 --> 00:50:38.643
It's okay, Mom. It's me.

618
00:50:39.340 --> 00:50:40.167
No!

619
00:50:41.559 --> 00:50:42.560
No! Let go of me!

620
00:50:42.604 --> 00:50:43.822
- Mom!
- Let go!


621
00:50:45.998 --> 00:50:47.348
Mom. It's okay. 
You'll be okay.

622
00:50:47.870 --> 00:50:49.567
No, no, no! Let go.

623
00:50:50.568 --> 00:50:51.656
No, please...

624
00:50:52.353 --> 00:50:53.223
Can you sit with her?

625
00:50:55.138 --> 00:50:56.748
Come, it's okay. No! [sobbing]

626
00:50:57.967 --> 00:50:59.534
[sobbing continues]

627
00:51:02.841 --> 00:51:04.756
[volume increases]

628
00:51:05.844 --> 00:51:08.064
[no audible dialogue]

629
00:51:29.433 --> 00:51:32.219
[sobbing] I'm sorry.

630
00:51:34.917 --> 00:51:36.005
Sorry!

631
00:51:45.667 --> 00:51:46.842
[music fades]

632
00:52:02.336 --> 00:52:04.599
[drawers rattling]

633
00:52:12.041 --> 00:52:13.825
[soft classical music playing]

634
00:52:32.627 --> 00:52:34.106
Don't pretend you
didn't hear that.


635
00:52:35.978 --> 00:52:37.980
You really shouldn't
indulge her that way.


636
00:52:38.023 --> 00:52:39.416
It's the last thing
she needs right now.


637
00:52:56.651 --> 00:52:57.434
What happened to you?

638
00:52:59.349 --> 00:53:03.222
What made you the heartless, horrible
human being you are now, hmm?


639
00:53:05.790 --> 00:53:10.012
Whatever happens in the end, wherever
you go, if you go to these caves,


640
00:53:10.491 --> 00:53:13.929
or you go to fucking hell,
I'm not coming with you.


641
00:53:27.464 --> 00:53:29.336
[clicks off]

642
00:53:32.295 --> 00:53:33.078
Dinner's ready!

643
00:53:36.952 --> 00:53:37.953
Is she all right?

644
00:53:38.562 --> 00:53:39.346
Yeah, she's fine.

645
00:53:41.086 --> 00:53:42.131
She understands.

646
00:53:43.437 --> 00:53:45.352
She understands
her mother's gone crazy?


647
00:53:47.354 --> 00:53:48.137
No, don't say that.

648
00:54:01.890 --> 00:54:03.108
That day...

649
00:54:06.068 --> 00:54:06.982
That day that you left...

650
00:54:11.247 --> 00:54:12.074
So proud of you.

651
00:54:15.207 --> 00:54:17.079
Telling your father
what you wanted.


652
00:54:19.516 --> 00:54:20.343
What you needed.

653
00:54:23.128 --> 00:54:24.303
God knows I never...

654
00:54:26.480 --> 00:54:27.655
I never could.

655
00:54:36.620 --> 00:54:37.926
But you're stronger than him.

656
00:54:41.495 --> 00:54:42.583
Don't let him destroy you.

657
00:54:50.242 --> 00:54:51.287
Come on, Mom.

658
00:54:51.679 --> 00:54:52.462
Ray.

659
00:54:55.639 --> 00:54:56.684
I know.

660
00:55:00.905 --> 00:55:02.472
I know who you are.

661
00:55:10.698 --> 00:55:11.481
My little boy.

662
00:55:13.527 --> 00:55:14.310
So...

663
00:55:15.703 --> 00:55:17.618
So proud of my little boy.

664
00:55:24.755 --> 00:55:28.193
Come on, Mom.
Let's get some rest, okay?


665
00:55:28.237 --> 00:55:29.281
Lay down.

666
00:55:45.776 --> 00:55:47.386
[opera music playing]

667
00:55:53.044 --> 00:55:53.828
[Raymond] Gina?

668
00:55:57.614 --> 00:55:58.746
[inhales sharply]

669
00:55:59.964 --> 00:56:01.096
[Raymond] Georgina!

670
00:56:38.394 --> 00:56:39.787
It was my father's favorite.

671
00:56:43.399 --> 00:56:45.009
Dad, please.
You've got to call them.


672
00:56:46.620 --> 00:56:49.144
Martin Beaty wasn't
a lot of things.


673
00:56:49.187 --> 00:56:51.755
[laughs] Well, he wasn't...

674
00:56:52.190 --> 00:56:54.584
he wasn't most things, actually,

675
00:56:55.324 --> 00:56:56.543
but he had great taste in music.

676
00:56:57.848 --> 00:56:58.501
Dad.

677
00:57:00.851 --> 00:57:01.635
He'll call, son.

678
00:57:02.897 --> 00:57:03.985
He will call.

679
00:57:05.421 --> 00:57:06.640
He has to. You know
all I've done for the senator.


680
00:57:07.554 --> 00:57:09.556
Now come on, eat.
Get some food in your stomach.


681
00:57:09.599 --> 00:57:10.818
We're going hunting
after dinner.


682
00:57:13.081 --> 00:57:14.125
Hunting?

683
00:57:15.779 --> 00:57:17.825
Dad, it's too dark to hunt.

684
00:57:19.087 --> 00:57:20.828
There's not gonna be anything
out there, it's too cold.


685
00:57:21.437 --> 00:57:23.265
- There'll be something.
- What is wrong with you?


686
00:57:23.613 --> 00:57:25.180
For God's sake, call them!

687
00:57:25.223 --> 00:57:27.095
We can't live like
this much longer!


688
00:57:28.575 --> 00:57:31.578
You will live however I want you
to live, do you understand me?


689
00:57:36.191 --> 00:57:37.888
Margot, my dear, please, come.

690
00:57:37.932 --> 00:57:39.368
Come sit with us, please. Eat.

691
00:57:41.675 --> 00:57:42.676
Please sit.

692
00:57:46.549 --> 00:57:48.420
I'm afraid that Gina's
not feeling too well.


693
00:57:48.682 --> 00:57:52.468
So, I apologize,
but the risotto is a little dry


694
00:57:52.511 --> 00:57:55.079
and, um, we're out of red,
sadly.


695
00:57:57.604 --> 00:57:58.822
You are all insane.

696
00:58:03.044 --> 00:58:04.306
I remember this part.

697
00:58:06.221 --> 00:58:08.658
- Foscari goes to visit his son in prison.
- I'm leaving, Fred. Tonight.


698
00:58:08.702 --> 00:58:13.445
He tells him that although he loves
him dearly, his duty must come first.


699
00:58:13.750 --> 00:58:15.360
[Margot]
Your mother isn't well, Fred.


700
00:58:16.405 --> 00:58:18.015
Somebody has to do something.

701
00:58:19.408 --> 00:58:20.627
She needs-
-[Raymond] She needs what?

702
00:58:22.933 --> 00:58:23.542
Help?

703
00:58:25.022 --> 00:58:26.458
Medical attention?

704
00:58:27.982 --> 00:58:30.419
I'm afraid, my dear,
she needs much more than that.


705
00:58:31.028 --> 00:58:32.682
She needs to talk to somebody.

706
00:58:32.726 --> 00:58:34.031
Well, you're the psychologist.

707
00:58:35.380 --> 00:58:36.425
Why not you?

708
00:58:37.818 --> 00:58:39.558
You tell her that everything
is going to be okay.


709
00:58:40.821 --> 00:58:43.171
Tell her how to find
inner peace and love.


710
00:58:43.824 --> 00:58:46.000
Tell her that the sun
will come back up tomorrow,


711
00:58:46.043 --> 00:58:47.871
tell her she didn't
kill her daughter.


712
00:58:50.700 --> 00:58:54.486
Do not tell me
what my wife needs.


713
00:58:55.313 --> 00:58:56.793
I know what she needs.

714
00:58:58.752 --> 00:59:02.886
She needs to be taken away from here
to someplace safe, someplace warm.


715
00:59:03.321 --> 00:59:05.106
She needs hope. She needs me.

716
00:59:08.239 --> 00:59:09.327
I'm going to get my gear.

717
00:59:10.024 --> 00:59:10.807
Meet me out front.

718
00:59:34.309 --> 00:59:35.223
Goodbye, Fred.[music fades]

719
01:00:06.820 --> 01:00:07.734
Turn it off. Turn it off.

720
01:00:29.451 --> 01:00:31.148
- Get down!
- [gunshot, glass shatters]


721
01:00:31.975 --> 01:00:34.369
[panting]

722
01:00:53.083 --> 01:00:53.867
Get out.

723
01:00:55.085 --> 01:00:56.826
Get out! Get out!

724
01:00:59.046 --> 01:01:00.090
Fred!

725
01:01:01.004 --> 01:01:02.223
Fred, open the door!

726
01:01:03.050 --> 01:01:03.790
Fred!

727
01:01:04.616 --> 01:01:05.400
No![banging on door]

728
01:01:07.054 --> 01:01:07.881
Fred!

729
01:01:08.359 --> 01:01:09.796
Fred, please let me in.

730
01:01:10.884 --> 01:01:12.407
I just want to go home.[sobs]

731
01:01:26.073 --> 01:01:27.465
[vehicle approaches]

732
01:02:04.502 --> 01:02:05.547
What are you doing here?

733
01:02:07.288 --> 01:02:10.334
When I heard your voice,
I knew I had to be with you.


734
01:02:11.858 --> 01:02:12.859
The stars, remember?

735
01:02:15.949 --> 01:02:17.167
It's getting bad out there.

736
01:02:18.952 --> 01:02:23.086
People in the streets,
they're not acting normal.


737
01:02:24.218 --> 01:02:25.219
This is it.

738
01:02:26.698 --> 01:02:29.005
It's happening, Ray,
I want to be with you.


739
01:02:33.575 --> 01:02:35.882
I come all this way to see you
and all you can do is shrug?


740
01:02:39.363 --> 01:02:40.364
What do you want, Brian?

741
01:02:42.279 --> 01:02:43.628
I want to come with you
to the caves.


742
01:02:45.369 --> 01:02:47.589
No. I'm not going
to any caves.


743
01:02:47.632 --> 01:02:50.505
Then I want to spend my last
few days with you, I don't care.


744
01:02:52.333 --> 01:02:53.377
We can't here.

745
01:02:54.509 --> 01:02:55.553
Then come away with me.

746
01:02:57.251 --> 01:02:59.296
Just you and me,
like we always talked about.


747
01:02:59.340 --> 01:03:00.558
I can't leave Clara,
you know that.


748
01:03:01.385 --> 01:03:02.430
I love you, Ray.

749
01:03:06.521 --> 01:03:07.696
[kissing]

750
01:03:12.135 --> 01:03:13.180
I can't.

751
01:03:14.964 --> 01:03:15.878
I'm so sorry.

752
01:03:16.966 --> 01:03:18.489
[Raymond] Whoever is out there,

753
01:03:18.533 --> 01:03:22.624
whoever you are, get off
my land or I'll shoot you!


754
01:03:24.539 --> 01:03:25.932
Please go. Please go. No, I won't!

755
01:03:25.975 --> 01:03:27.281
Do you hear me?

756
01:03:27.324 --> 01:03:29.152
No, I'm not leaving you.
I won't go without you.


757
01:03:29.196 --> 01:03:30.588
Just go! Please leave!

758
01:03:31.198 --> 01:03:31.981
Just go!

759
01:03:34.462 --> 01:03:35.506
Just go.

760
01:03:38.248 --> 01:03:39.032
You're a coward.

761
01:03:42.513 --> 01:03:43.427
[Raymond] You hear me?

762
01:03:46.561 --> 01:03:47.779
[exhales deeply]

763
01:03:49.172 --> 01:03:49.999
[exhales deeply]

764
01:04:36.393 --> 01:04:38.439
[whistling]

765
01:04:49.015 --> 01:04:50.494
[fingers squeaking on walls]

766
01:04:58.459 --> 01:05:00.243
[heavy breathing]

767
01:05:55.081 --> 01:05:56.560
[telephone rings]

768
01:06:04.916 --> 01:06:05.700
Hello?

769
01:06:06.483 --> 01:06:07.354
Hello?

770
01:06:08.616 --> 01:06:09.486
Bill.

771
01:06:10.661 --> 01:06:11.793
I'm so glad you called.

772
01:06:12.489 --> 01:06:14.187
I knew you would call!

773
01:06:14.535 --> 01:06:15.144
I knew it, Bill!

774
01:06:15.623 --> 01:06:16.885
Uh...

775
01:06:17.146 --> 01:06:19.844
[laughs] We're packed.
We're ready to go.


776
01:06:21.455 --> 01:06:22.108
What?

777
01:06:25.372 --> 01:06:26.155
I don't understand.

778
01:06:29.245 --> 01:06:32.118
What-- What do you mean?
What about the caves?


779
01:06:37.297 --> 01:06:38.124
Yes.

780
01:06:44.391 --> 01:06:45.131
[beeps]

781
01:07:07.675 --> 01:07:08.937
[hinges creak]

782
01:07:16.727 --> 01:07:18.120
[engine starts]

783
01:07:37.792 --> 01:07:39.141
[engine revving]

784
01:07:49.543 --> 01:07:50.848
[garage door opening]

785
01:08:09.650 --> 01:08:11.173
[tires squeal]

786
01:09:00.657 --> 01:09:02.268
[music playing on radio]

787
01:10:00.674 --> 01:10:01.718
What time is it?

788
01:10:02.893 --> 01:10:04.155
It's eight in the morning.

789
01:10:07.507 --> 01:10:08.334
What happened?

790
01:10:09.030 --> 01:10:10.248
You tell me.

791
01:10:10.727 --> 01:10:11.902
Ray said you had an accident.

792
01:10:12.425 --> 01:10:13.208
In your car.

793
01:10:15.036 --> 01:10:16.080
Where were you going?

794
01:10:17.343 --> 01:10:19.170
Well, we were
running out of food...


795
01:10:21.434 --> 01:10:25.220
and I thought I could
find some somewhere.


796
01:10:35.883 --> 01:10:37.058
The lights don't work anymore.

797
01:10:40.453 --> 01:10:41.802
Ray said he heard
the phone ring.


798
01:10:42.716 --> 01:10:43.760
Who was it?

799
01:10:45.936 --> 01:10:46.981
Was it Bill?

800
01:10:47.938 --> 01:10:48.983
What did he say?

801
01:11:01.604 --> 01:11:03.214
They're coming for us. Tomorrow.

802
01:11:05.956 --> 01:11:07.175
It's over.

803
01:11:12.833 --> 01:11:14.051
It's gonna be cold.

804
01:11:15.792 --> 01:11:18.316
We should all stay together by
the fire until they come tomorrow.


805
01:11:22.756 --> 01:11:23.800
Mom, we need you.

806
01:11:29.806 --> 01:11:30.894
[Margot screams]

807
01:11:34.028 --> 01:11:35.464
Okay. It's time. It's time.

808
01:11:35.508 --> 01:11:37.118
What, here? Now? Yes.

809
01:11:37.423 --> 01:11:38.815
Everybody out! 
Everybody out!

810
01:11:39.512 --> 01:11:40.991
No, no, no. Fred, you stay.

811
01:11:41.035 --> 01:11:42.123
I need your help, come on.Okay.

812
01:11:42.732 --> 01:11:43.472
Let's go.

813
01:11:44.299 --> 01:11:45.605
[groans]

814
01:11:46.344 --> 01:11:47.128
Will she be all right?

815
01:11:50.871 --> 01:11:51.654
Yeah, she'll be fine.

816
01:11:54.396 --> 01:11:56.398
Daddy, are they really
coming for us tomorrow?


817
01:11:57.225 --> 01:11:58.705
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

818
01:12:00.924 --> 01:12:01.925
How much stuff can I pack?

819
01:12:03.144 --> 01:12:04.188
As much as you want.

820
01:12:13.546 --> 01:12:14.764
I'm gonna go finish packing.

821
01:12:23.033 --> 01:12:24.252
So what are you gonna do?

822
01:12:24.992 --> 01:12:26.254
Just gonna kill us all?

823
01:12:39.136 --> 01:12:40.181
[sighs]

824
01:12:42.226 --> 01:12:43.532
We are a bunch of cowards,
aren't we?


825
01:12:45.316 --> 01:12:47.231
[groans][Gina speaks French]

826
01:12:49.146 --> 01:12:50.060
Is she coming?

827
01:12:56.719 --> 01:12:58.068
[rattling]

828
01:13:12.387 --> 01:13:13.780
[squeaking]

829
01:13:53.602 --> 01:13:55.212
Do you think there'll be
cute boys there?


830
01:13:55.996 --> 01:13:57.954
At the caves.Mmm.

831
01:13:59.695 --> 01:14:01.610
Mmm. There'll be lots
of cute boys with that one.


832
01:14:01.871 --> 01:14:02.655
Good.

833
01:14:03.394 --> 01:14:05.440
[speaking French]

834
01:14:05.962 --> 01:14:07.050
Margot, push.

835
01:14:07.094 --> 01:14:09.139
[screams]

836
01:14:11.794 --> 01:14:13.013
She's coming.

837
01:14:14.928 --> 01:14:15.798
It's okay.

838
01:14:32.685 --> 01:14:34.121
[Margot screams]

839
01:14:36.210 --> 01:14:37.515
[both speaking French]

840
01:14:43.347 --> 01:14:44.435
Push.

841
01:14:45.523 --> 01:14:46.916
[groans]

842
01:14:55.533 --> 01:14:57.448
Oh, my God. I see the head.

843
01:14:59.842 --> 01:15:00.930
Margot, push!

844
01:15:00.974 --> 01:15:03.237
- [wailing]
- [shouts]


845
01:15:05.718 --> 01:15:08.068
- [Margot cries out]
- [baby cries]


846
01:15:08.111 --> 01:15:09.373
Okay. Okay.

847
01:15:09.417 --> 01:15:10.679
[baby cries]

848
01:15:17.817 --> 01:15:19.470
[both laugh]

849
01:15:19.775 --> 01:15:20.820
Wow.

850
01:15:22.038 --> 01:15:22.778
You're an aunt.

851
01:15:23.170 --> 01:15:24.214
I'm an aunt.

852
01:15:26.521 --> 01:15:27.914
That makes you an uncle.

853
01:15:32.658 --> 01:15:34.529
[Gina] Okay, okay.

854
01:15:34.572 --> 01:15:35.965
Claudine.

855
01:15:36.879 --> 01:15:37.924
It's okay.

856
01:15:40.491 --> 01:15:42.755
[laughs]

857
01:16:00.947 --> 01:16:01.861
[shudders]

858
01:16:03.253 --> 01:16:04.472
Jesus.

859
01:16:24.710 --> 01:16:25.536
How's the baby?

860
01:16:27.016 --> 01:16:27.887
Healthy.

861
01:16:28.844 --> 01:16:29.758
That's good.

862
01:16:32.674 --> 01:16:33.457
That's good.

863
01:16:36.069 --> 01:16:37.113
Look at you.

864
01:16:40.421 --> 01:16:42.423
I remember the moment
when I first saw you.


865
01:16:44.512 --> 01:16:46.340
You were so beautiful, perfect.

866
01:16:48.603 --> 01:16:49.952
I'd never seen anything
so perfect.


867
01:16:52.999 --> 01:16:54.957
It was the first moment
in my life that I felt...


868
01:17:00.658 --> 01:17:01.442
joy.

869
01:17:04.401 --> 01:17:05.446
Thank you, Gina.

870
01:17:10.233 --> 01:17:11.278
For choosing me.

871
01:17:13.149 --> 01:17:14.194
For everything.

872
01:17:31.951 --> 01:17:33.474
I'll go get dinner together.

873
01:17:57.367 --> 01:17:58.412
She's cold.

874
01:18:04.766 --> 01:18:06.028
It'll all be over tomorrow.

875
01:18:19.607 --> 01:18:20.477
[sighs]

876
01:18:24.351 --> 01:18:25.395
We made it, Dad.

877
01:18:28.137 --> 01:18:28.921
It's over.

878
01:18:44.893 --> 01:18:45.894
[sliding door opens]

879
01:18:46.677 --> 01:18:48.462
[door closes][Ray shivering]

880
01:18:48.505 --> 01:18:49.680
Where did you go?

881
01:19:57.009 --> 01:19:58.140
[screams]

882
01:20:00.055 --> 01:20:01.883
Dad. What's going on?

883
01:20:04.320 --> 01:20:05.974
[Claudine cries]

884
01:20:13.112 --> 01:20:14.940
During different times,
I would have rung the doorbell.


885
01:20:16.550 --> 01:20:17.594
What do you want?

886
01:20:18.030 --> 01:20:19.422
Oh, we aren't here
to harm anyone.


887
01:20:20.597 --> 01:20:22.208
Enough harm's been done
already, wouldn't you agree?


888
01:20:22.599 --> 01:20:23.731
We don't have much.

889
01:20:28.605 --> 01:20:30.042
[Claudine whimpers]

890
01:20:31.043 --> 01:20:34.437
What kind of a husband
and a father would I be


891
01:20:34.481 --> 01:20:36.396
if I didn't provide
for my family?


892
01:20:38.615 --> 01:20:39.442
Food's in the basement.

893
01:20:45.796 --> 01:20:47.233
No! That's mine!

894
01:20:47.276 --> 01:20:48.190
Clara, be quiet.

895
01:20:50.714 --> 01:20:52.673
- Daddy, it's for the caves.
- I said be quiet!


896
01:20:52.716 --> 01:20:53.761
No, no.

897
01:20:55.415 --> 01:20:56.198
It's all right.

898
01:21:01.899 --> 01:21:04.815
Hey. You can tell me.

899
01:21:07.993 --> 01:21:10.038
Is your daddy taking you
somewhere, princess?


900
01:21:10.604 --> 01:21:11.561
Yeah? Mm-hmm.

901
01:21:13.302 --> 01:21:14.347
Where's that?

902
01:21:19.221 --> 01:21:20.353
To the safe place.

903
01:21:22.442 --> 01:21:23.486
The caves.

904
01:21:26.533 --> 01:21:28.230
[Claudine whimpers]

905
01:21:28.926 --> 01:21:29.840
What caves?

906
01:21:37.239 --> 01:21:38.197
You got a way out?

907
01:21:38.588 --> 01:21:39.633
There's no room for you.

908
01:21:39.676 --> 01:21:40.982
Clara, just be quiet.

909
01:21:42.592 --> 01:21:44.507
What caves,
you son of a bitch?


910
01:21:44.551 --> 01:21:45.856
Dad, just tell them
about the caves.


911
01:21:46.422 --> 01:21:48.120
Dad. Tell them.

912
01:21:51.471 --> 01:21:52.602
There are no caves.

913
01:21:56.650 --> 01:21:57.694
There never were.

914
01:22:06.486 --> 01:22:07.139
- [grunts]
- [Margot gasps]


915
01:22:07.878 --> 01:22:08.923
[man] Caves...

916
01:22:09.532 --> 01:22:10.533
Let's go.

917
01:22:11.621 --> 01:22:13.884
[Claudine whimpers]

918
01:22:29.552 --> 01:22:33.730
[Claudine fusses]

919
01:22:41.738 --> 01:22:44.437
You have a very civilized
household here.


920
01:22:44.480 --> 01:22:48.136
You should see some of the places
we've visited, just animals.


921
01:22:54.186 --> 01:22:55.578
My car is in the garage.

922
01:23:00.627 --> 01:23:02.933
You could get in. Just go.

923
01:23:05.153 --> 01:23:06.241
Get away from here.

924
01:23:06.676 --> 01:23:07.938
- [gunshot]
- [gasps]


925
01:23:07.982 --> 01:23:09.810
- [gunshot]
- [Claudine whimpers]


926
01:23:29.308 --> 01:23:30.352
Where is he?

927
01:23:30.831 --> 01:23:32.267
What did you do with him? He's dead.

928
01:23:32.920 --> 01:23:34.356
He was never gonna save you.

929
01:23:34.791 --> 01:23:35.792
He couldn't!

930
01:23:36.271 --> 01:23:37.403
Nobody can.

931
01:23:40.710 --> 01:23:41.755
It's over.

932
01:23:44.758 --> 01:23:46.325
[panting]

933
01:24:33.720 --> 01:24:36.157
[whimpering]

934
01:24:41.771 --> 01:24:42.555
Where are you going?

935
01:26:15.169 --> 01:26:16.170
I don't feel well.

936
01:26:20.000 --> 01:26:21.044
I know.

937
01:26:23.873 --> 01:26:24.918
I'm scared.

938
01:26:26.354 --> 01:26:27.137
Don't be.

939
01:26:28.530 --> 01:26:29.575
Will it hurt?

940
01:26:33.143 --> 01:26:33.927
I promise it won't.

941
01:26:38.888 --> 01:26:40.107
Do you think
there's a heaven?


942
01:26:40.673 --> 01:26:41.456
[Gina]
I think so.


943
01:26:42.675 --> 01:26:43.719
I hope so.

944
01:26:49.551 --> 01:26:50.770
What do you think it's like?

945
01:26:51.684 --> 01:26:53.555
[Gina] Well, I think
it's pretty amazing.


946
01:26:55.209 --> 01:26:56.993
It's warm, but not too warm.

947
01:26:59.779 --> 01:27:01.433
And all your
favorite food is there.


948
01:27:02.695 --> 01:27:03.739
And candy.

949
01:27:05.567 --> 01:27:06.351
Chocolate.

950
01:27:07.090 --> 01:27:08.135
Lots of chocolate.

951
01:27:09.745 --> 01:27:12.008
And there's water everywhere
for you to swim in it.


952
01:27:13.053 --> 01:27:14.924
Water that cradles
you from head to toe.


953
01:27:15.664 --> 01:27:16.970
You can dance...

954
01:27:19.320 --> 01:27:21.061
all day long if you want to.

955
01:27:24.847 --> 01:27:26.849
And there's no troubles
or worries...


956
01:27:33.552 --> 01:27:34.379
just quiet.

957
01:27:37.991 --> 01:27:39.079
Peace.

958
01:27:42.561 --> 01:27:44.476
And all your favorite people
are there.


959
01:27:52.875 --> 01:27:53.833
Abbey will be there.

960
01:27:58.620 --> 01:27:59.795
Oh, yes.

961
01:28:02.972 --> 01:28:04.017
Abbey will be there.

962
01:29:00.726 --> 01:29:02.597
[birds chirping]

963
01:29:41.157 --> 01:29:42.637
[door hinges creak]

964
01:31:10.507 --> 01:31:12.379
[folk-rock music playing]

965
01:33:47.186 --> 01:33:49.188
[song ends]